The paper deals with a fundamental problem in distributed computing, specifically the Maximal Independent Set selection problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. 

The algorithm proposed by the authors is inspired by the study of developing cells in the fly, which suggests a connection to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

The paper also incorporates feedback from neighbouring nodes, which suggests a connection to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. 

The paper proposes a new algorithm that achieves optimal efficiency, which suggests a connection to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper deals with graph theory and optimization, which suggests a connection to the Game Theory and Economics (cs.GT) sub-category.
